# LLaMEA Camera Lens Optimization Workspace

This workspace combines the **BLADE Framework** (for Large Language Model Evolutionary Algorithm generation) with the **Camera Lens Simulation** engine (an objective physics sandbox). 

Our goal is to evolve novel black-box optimization algorithms capable of navigating the highly non-linear, mixed continuous-discrete optical design landscape.

## 📂 Repository Structure

The workspace is divided into two distinct but linked Python packages:

* `/blade-framework`: The meta-evolution engine handling LLM prompts, algorithm generation, BBOB benchmarking, and experiment logging.
* `/camera-lens-simulation`: The physics engine and optical design objective functions (e.g., the Double Gauss simulator), exposed as the `lensgopt` package.

## 🚀 Initialization & Setup

We strictly use [`uv`](https://github.com/astral-sh/uv) for lightning-fast, reproducible dependency management. **Do not use standard `pip` or `conda` for environment setup.**

### 1. Prerequisites
Ensure you have Python 3.10+ and `uv` installed on your system:
```bash
curl -LsSf [https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh](https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh) | sh
